<p>A <b>mathematical joke</b> is a form of <a href="/wiki/Humor" title="Humor" class="mw-redirect">humor</a> which relies on aspects of <a href="/wiki/Mathematics" title="Mathematics">mathematics</a> or a <a href="/wiki/Stereotype" title="Stereotype">stereotype</a> of <a href="/wiki/Mathematicians" title="Mathematicians" class="mw-redirect">mathematicians</a> to <a href="/wiki/Derive" title="Derive">derive</a> humor. The humor may come from a pun, or from a double meaning of a mathematical term. It may also come from a lay person's misunderstanding of a mathematical concept (which is not wholly unexpected). These jokes are frequently inaccessible to those without a mathematical bent.</p>
